Remove duplicate person handling in EditCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the EditCommand handles editing a person to a duplicate one.
It operates on the assumption that the name is the primary identifier of
a person, and two people with the same name are duplicates.
However, we have changed the person's primary identifier to be
matriculation number, as it is possible to have different people with
the same name, but matriculation number is unique.
Furthermore, the current implementation of EditCommand never modifies
the matriculation number. Therefore, we can guarantee that EditCommand
will never turn an existing person into a duplicate person, as
the person's matriculation number will remain the same as when
the person was added.
Hence, We can safely remove handling of duplicate person in EditCommand.

commitResults.messageTitle: Abstract Course code and Course Name to classes.
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, course code and course name in Course are stored as strings,
with their formats and validation fields and methods stored in Course. We
should create classes for course code and course name, similar to
Name and Email, used to store information for Person. This makes it
easier to parse commands for Course, as we do not have to manually
perform validation during parsing Course commands.

now move the validation tests to their own course code and course name
test classes.
